title: PyTorch ImportError
body_html:
Issue description

ImportError Traceback (most recent call last)
in ()
----> 1 import torch

/usr/local/lib/python3.5/dist-packages/torch/init.py in ()
78 pass
79
---> 80 from torch._C import *
81
82 all += [name for name in dir(_C)

ImportError: /usr/local/lib/python3.5/dist-packages/torch/_C.cpython-35m-x86_64-linux-gnu.so: undefined symbol: _ZN2at8demangleB5cxx11EPKc

Code example

$ ipython3
Python 3.5.2 (default, Nov 23 2017, 16:37:01)
Type 'copyright', 'credits' or 'license' for more information
IPython 6.3.1 -- An enhanced Interactive Python. Type '?' for help.

In [1]: import torch

System Info

when I tried to collect the system informatiion with collect_evn.py, I faced the error as follows .
[1] 3854 segmentation fault (core dumped) python3 collect_env.py

  • PyTorch or Caffe2: PyTorch
  • How you installed PyTorch (conda, pip, source): source
  • Build command you used (if compiling from source): python3 setup.py install
  • OS: Ubuntu 16.04
  • PyTorch version: 0.4
  • Python version: 3.5
  • CUDA/cuDNN version: 9.0/7.5
  • GPU models and configuration: GTX 1080Ti
  • GCC version (if compiling from source): 4.6
  • CMake version: 3.11

## Issue description
ImportError                               Traceback (most recent call last)
<ipython-input-1-eb42ca6e4af3> in <module>()
----> 1 import torch

/usr/local/lib/python3.5/dist-packages/torch/__init__.py in <module>()
     78     pass
     79 
---> 80 from torch._C import *
     81 
     82 __all__ += [name for name in dir(_C)

ImportError: /usr/local/lib/python3.5/dist-packages/torch/_C.cpython-35m-x86_64-linux-gnu.so: undefined symbol: _ZN2at8demangleB5cxx11EPKc

## Code example
> $ ipython3                                                      
Python 3.5.2 (default, Nov 23 2017, 16:37:01) 
Type 'copyright', 'credits' or 'license' for more information
IPython 6.3.1 -- An enhanced Interactive Python. Type '?' for help.

In [1]: import torch

## System Info
when I tried to collect the system informatiion with collect_evn.py, I faced the error as follows .
[1]    3854 segmentation fault (core dumped)  python3 collect_env.py

- PyTorch or Caffe2: PyTorch
- How you installed PyTorch (conda, pip, source): source
- Build command you used (if compiling from source): python3 setup.py install
- OS: Ubuntu 16.04
- PyTorch version: 0.4
- Python version: 3.5
- CUDA/cuDNN version: 9.0/7.5
- GPU models and configuration: GTX 1080Ti
- GCC version (if compiling from source): 4.6
- CMake version: 3.11
